1. The "Open Core" Strategy
If you are building a platform like Abacus DeepAgent, you might want to apply this MIT license to your Client SDKs and Connectors (the parts you want everyone to build on), while keeping your Core Factorizer Engine or Proprietary HAC Algorithms under a more restrictive or commercial license.

2. Patent Clause Note
The MIT license is very short and does not contain an explicit patent grant (unlike the Apache 2.0 license). Since you have active patents (like the "Neural Band-Aid" and NCI Formula), using MIT for the code means you are giving permission to use the code, but you aren't necessarily signing away your underlying patent rights for other implementations.

3. Attribution (The Jewel Point)
The line Copyright (c) 2025 bhineswaveformer6 is your Provenance Anchor. In your Epoch Explorer, every time this code is used to mint an asset, this copyright string serves as the "Genesis Block" of the intellectual lineage.

4. Where to place this
To ensure your "Virtual Workforce" agents recognize this:

LICENSE file: Place the full text in a file named LICENSE in your root directory.
File Headers: Add a short comment at the top of your critical files (like creature-engine.ts or FactorizerTable.tsx):
typescript
Copy
/* 
